 "verbal noun of شَكَلَ (šakala) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a dubious or confused matter"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "an ear ornament of pearl or silver"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "plural of شِكَال (šikāl, “hobble”)", "tags": ["form-of", "plural"]}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n22848", "headword_ar": "شَكْلٌ", "root": "$kl", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$abapN", "text_ar": "شَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A likeness, resemblance,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "semblance;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "a well-known signification of the latter word, but one which I do not find unequivocally assigned to it in its proper art. in any of the lexicons]. (AA, K, TA. [In the CK, and in my MS. copy of the K, in the place of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al$~abahu", "text_ar": "الشَّبَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as the first explanation of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al$~akolu", "text_ar": "الشَّكْلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the K accord. to the TA, we find"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al$~ibohu", "text_ar": "الشِّبْهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but that the explanation which I have given is correct, is shown by what here follows.]) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY fulaAnK $akolN mino A^abiyhi", "text_ar": "فِى فُلَانٍ شَكْلٌ مِنْ اَبِيهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$abahN", "text_ar": "شَبَهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In such a one is a likeness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "resemblance, of his father"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (AA, TA:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino A^abiyhi", "text_ar": "مِنْ اَبِيهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiyhi A^a$okalapN", "text_ar": "فِيهِ اَشْكَلَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ukolapN", "text_ar": "شُكْلَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AA, O, K, TA)"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1587}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aAkilN", "text_ar": "شَاكِلٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (O, K, TA,) [likewise] meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$abahN", "text_ar": "شَبَهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (AA, O, K, TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mu$aAbahapN", "text_ar": "مُشَابَهَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TK:) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aAkilapN", "text_ar": "شَاكِلَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$akolN", "text_ar": "شَكْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in the sense of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$abahN", "text_ar": "شَبَهٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (K, TA;) [for] one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA EalaY $aAkilapi", "text_ar": "هٰذَا عَلَى شَاكِلَةِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abiyhi", "text_ar": "اَبِيهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$abahihi", "text_ar": "شَبَهِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is accordant to the likeness of his father"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mivaAlN", "text_ar": "مِثَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA EalaY $akoli h`*aA", "text_ar": "هٰذَا عَلَى شَكْلِ هٰذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ElY", "text_ar": "على"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mivaAlihi", "text_ar": "مِثَالِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is according to the model,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pattern,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the mode,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "manner, of this"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "shape, form,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "figure,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Suwrap", "text_ar": "صُورَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) of a thing;"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as is perceived by the senses;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as is imagined:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "form"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hayoy^ap", "text_ar": "هَيْيَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "), of a body,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "caused by the entire contents' being included by one boundary, as in the case of a sphere;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by several boundaries, as in those bodies that have several angles"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sides, such as have four"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as have six"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[&c.]: so says Ibn-El-Kemál: (TA:) pl. [of pauc., in this and in other senses,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$okaAlN", "text_ar": "اَشْكَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ukuwlN", "text_ar": "شُكُولٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) ―         -b4-  [It often means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A kind, sort,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "variety,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of animals, plants, food, &c.] ―         -b5-  [And The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "likeness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "way"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "manner, of the actions"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a person:] it is said in a trad. respecting the description of the Prophet,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saA^alotu", "text_ar": "سَاَلْتُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abiY Eano $akolihi", "text_ar": "اَبِى عَنْ شَكْلِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I asked my father respecting the likeness of his actions,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "respecting what was like his actions;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "accord. to IAmb: or, accord. to Az,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "respecting his particular way, course, mode,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "manner, of acting,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "conduct:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O:) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aAkilapN", "text_ar": "شَاكِلَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[likewise, and more commonly,] signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a particular way, course, mode,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "manner, of acting,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "conduct;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, K, TA;) as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kul~N yaEomalu EalaY $aAkilatihi", "text_ar": "كُلٌّ يَعْمَلُ عَلَى شَاكِلَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O, TA,) in the Kur [xvii. 86], (O, TA,) i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Every one does according to his particular way,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c., (Ibn-'Arafeh, S, O, Bd, Jel, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that is suitable to his state in respect of right direction"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of error,"}, {