َمِنْ شَكْلِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is of what is loved by me and of what is suitable to me"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (K, TA:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "layosa $akoluhu mino $akoliY", "text_ar": "لَيْسَ شَكْلُهُ مِنْ شَكْلِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What is suitable to him is not of what is suitable to me"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) [And hence, app.,] one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA$akoliY wa$akoluhu", "text_ar": "مَاشَكْلِى وَشَكْلُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What is my case and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[what is]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its, case?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because of his, or its, remoteness from me. (T and TA voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^um~N", "text_ar": "اُمٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b7-  And sing. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$okaAlN", "text_ar": "اَشْكَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(L, K, TA) signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Discordant affairs"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "objects of want, concerning things on account of which one imposes upon himself difficulty and for which one is anxious:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, TA:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dubious,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "confused, affairs:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "discordant, and dubious,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "confused, affairs."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K. [In the CK,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Almu$ak~alap", "text_ar": "المُشَكَّلَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is erroneously put for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Almu$okilap", "text_ar": "المُشْكِلَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".])       -A2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A like;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mivolN", "text_ar": "مِثْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K;) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ikolN", "text_ar": "شِكْلٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (O, K:) or, as some say, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "like"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of another"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in nature"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "constitution:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb: [and accord. to Er-Rághib, it seems that the attribute properly denoted by it is congruity between two persons in respect of the way or manner of acting or conduct: but in the passage in which this is expressed in the TA, I find erasures and alterations which render it doubtful:]) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$okaAlN", "text_ar": "اَشْكَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K *) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$ukuwlN", "text_ar": "شُكُولٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as above]. (S, O, Msb, K. *) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA $akolu h`*aA", "text_ar": "هٰذَا شَكْلُ هٰذَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "This is the like of this."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN $akolu fulaAnK", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ شَكْلُ فُلَانٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one is the like of such a one in his several states"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "conditions"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[&c.]. (TA.) In the saying in the Kur [xxxviii. 58],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waA=xaru mino $akolihi", "text_ar": "وَا=خَرُ مِنْ شَكْلِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (O, TA,) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And other"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "punishment"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the like thereof,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj, TA,) Mujáhid read ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mn $ikolihi", "text_ar": "من شِكْلِهِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (O, TA.)       -A3-  Also sing. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$okaAlN", "text_ar": "اَشْكَالٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifying, (O, K,) accord. to IAar, (O,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Certain ornaments"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "consisting of pearls"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of silver,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "resembling one another, worn as ear-drops by women:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, K:) or, as some say, the sing. signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a certain thing which girls,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "young women, used to append to their hair, of pearls"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of silver."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O.)       -A4-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A species of plant,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, O, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "diversified in colour,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "yellow and red."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, O, K.)       -A5-  [And The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "various syllabical signs,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "vowel-points &c., by which the pronunciation of words is indicated and restricted:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "originally an inf. n., and therefore thus used in a pl. sense.]       -A6-  See also the next paragraph."}], "source_refs": ["AA", "TA", "O", "K", "TK", "S", "Bd", "L", "Lth", "Zj", "IAar"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}